Note: It seems that CK will in some cases (particularly XPRI) create references with initial master load id offset from 08 forward as if every official master were loaded before it even if they weren't when generating the plugin from within CK. Update: actually this may not be true and I just forgot that I had initially loaded all 8 esms in my test.
---

Generating visibility for cells without precombined references results in non-combined visibility being generated. This is why some cells show updated vis timestamps and XPRI references but no XCRI data. This type of thing would occur in vanilla files due to -generateprevisdata operating on a larger or different set of cells then what -generateprecombined operated on.

