CDX issue: For XCRI/XPRI data which has been regenerated and merged into an esm which *has* a CDX file, one must issue -BuildCDX:<esm> in order for said newly generated precombined and previs cell records to even be used. Not doing this will result in the typical flashing statics preculling issues. Doing nothing at all but simply -BuildCDX on the same master resolves the preculling issues so one can speculate that the CDX file has old cell data vs what's actually in the esm.

---

Attempting to check in precombined or previs changes from CK whilst using a delocalized ESM will result in those changes never being merged and the precombined timestamp being deleted. If the ESM is localized they will be merged. This doesn't seem to affect -checkinplugin.

